100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 6, 1926, the world watched as the United States and Britain engaged in discussions regarding naval disarmament, emphasizing the growing global concern over military expenditures. In Europe, political tensions flared as France faced internal strife, with protests against government policies escalating in Paris. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, the discovery of a new treatment for tuberculosis sparked hope among medical experts.
